    Scope and Contents
INSTITUTE OF INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS COLLECTION
Pease, doctor of medicine, discusses his career in the IIAA: work in Peru, Costa Rica, and Paraguay; public health policies and programs; medical developments; living in different cultures and environments; diseases, vaccines, and medications. He also discusses Agency for International Development central office in Washington D.C. and its policies, programs, and relations with Vietnam, Thailand, and Latin American  countries. Also discusses history and observations of IIAA and its successor agencies as well as AID and NIH. He also discusses his family, Army service, and attitudes.Memoir, 78 pp.
Interview by James D. Williams, 1985
